comments.text:
This is a very innovative, mathematical way of representing music. It 
accurately states the relationships of notes in a particular key signature. 
This video shows the mathematical reason behind thirds, fifths, and 
sevenths and why, when combined, they produce musical wavelength harmony 
that we easily can identify. The way she shows harmonies of different notes 
combined with different rhythms is very entertaining and can be educational 
to those who are looking to understand music more thoroughly.﻿
